Yummmm. Made this tonight for the 2 of us. 2 large chicken breasts, but the whole sauce recipe. I did adjust a bit after reading the reviews. Marinated the chicken breasts in olive oil/garlic/fresh thyme while I was preparing the other ingredients. Reduced the broth to 3/4 cup, used non-fat Greek yogurt instead of heavy cream, added 1 tsp hot dry mustard, and added only about 1 Tbsp of fresh chopped chives at the end. The chicken breasts I had were huge so I sliced one for the 2 of us, plated it and poured the sauce over. Delicious. And now we have the other breast and sauce to try "cadapi09's" suggestion for the leftovers.

