This was so good!! I took the chicken breast and put in a ziplock bag. Added a little olive oil, garlic, Thyme & dill and let it marinade. The dill was excellent in it. Once marinaded, I added peanut oil to pan and browned chicken lightly. Added the "chive" tops from green onion and sauteed some more. To the wine I added the dijon and stirred to combine slightly and poured over chicken and let come to a boil. Turned down heat and added the chicken stock mixed with cornstarch and let come to another boil. Poured the whipping cream on and let simmer while I made some herb chicken flavored couscous and steamed up some green beans. Very easy even for me. Would def make aganin

